and then you turn left.

235
00:23:48,153 --> 00:23:54,072
Oh, like hell l'm editorialising. Look, it
happened in a room full of press and ClA.

236
00:23:54,200 --> 00:23:59,158
How do l know they were ClA? Because
they wore name tags. What do you think?

237
00:23:59,288 --> 00:24:02,491
We're backing a fascist government.
l know that's not news,

238
00:24:02,624 --> 00:24:04,867
but see if you can find an angle, huh?

239
00:24:05,002 --> 00:24:10,292
Alex, there's fascist and there's fascist.
Let's not use words like that, OK?

240
00:24:10,424 --> 00:24:14,552
No, we don't have any pictures of Rafael,
because nobody knows where he is.

241
00:24:14,678 --> 00:24:19,055
Anybody crazy enough to go and look
for him is gonna get his nuts shot off.

242
00:24:20,058 --> 00:24:22,346
Same to you, Charlie.

243
00:24:22,477 --> 00:24:24,516
- What do you want?
- We've met, Alex.

244
00:24:24,646 --> 00:24:28,857
Hub Kittle, from Lewitsky and Knupp,
New York, public relations.

245
00:24:28,984 --> 00:24:31,521
- l have a client down here.
- Who's your client?

246
00:24:31,652 --> 00:24:33,692
President Somoza.

247
00:24:34,489 --> 00:24:37,490
Yeah, l know, l know,
but there's an untold story here.

248
00:24:37,617 --> 00:24:39,989
The man has a point of view too, right?

249
00:24:40,953 --> 00:24:42,993
Right.

250
00:24:43,622 --> 00:24:47,537
You're, uh... Price, right? Russel?

251
00:24:49,961 --> 00:24:53,794
l need to know whether Russian or
Cuban-made guns were brought in.

252
00:24:53,924 --> 00:24:57,174
lf the guerillas had help,
the war would have ended long ago.

253
00:24:57,302 --> 00:25:00,219
- Well, that's fine, but we need proof.
- Claire!

254
00:25:00,347 --> 00:25:02,672
lt's your daughter from Los Angeles.

255
00:25:07,103 --> 00:25:09,013
Hello.

256
00:25:09,147 --> 00:25:11,389
Hello, darling. How are you?

257
00:25:12,483 --> 00:25:15,319
Has your grandmother
spoiled you silly by now?

258
00:25:15,444 --> 00:25:17,687
She has? Great.

259
00:25:19,073 --> 00:25:22,608
Yes, l got the letter
with the picture of your dress.

260
00:25:22,743 --> 00:25:25,863
You don't think it's cut a little too low?

261
00:25:26,539 --> 00:25:29,788
You don't, huh? Well, l do.

262
00:25:48,977 --> 00:25:51,183
Gringo.

263
00:25:51,312 --> 00:25:52,557
You're under arrest.

264
00:25:52,688 --> 00:25:57,849
l'm a journalist. Periodista. Periodista.
Here, l got my passport.

265
00:25:57,985 --> 00:25:59,812
You take too many pictures.

266
00:25:59,945 --> 00:26:01,985
Periodista.

267
00:26:06,952 --> 00:26:10,451
Wake up, Priest, son of a whore.

268
00:26:24,594 --> 00:26:26,966
Cigarrillo?

269
00:26:27,097 --> 00:26:29,136
Sí.

270
00:26:32,935 --> 00:26:35,142
You're a priest, huh? A padre?

271
00:26:42,445 --> 00:26:44,899
What are you doing here?

272
00:26:47,115 --> 00:26:49,951
The government accused me
of knowing Rafael.

273
00:26:51,161 --> 00:26:53,652
Governments are always wrong, huh?

274
00:26:58,585 --> 00:27:01,041
- Who are you?
- Periodista.

275
00:27:04,758 --> 00:27:07,462
l'd like to find Rafael myself.

276
00:27:07,593 --> 00:27:11,425
- Whose side are you on?
- l don't take sides, l take pictures.

277
00:27:11,806 --> 00:27:13,846
No side?

278
00:27:27,696 --> 00:27:30,152
Go home.

279
00:27:43,962 --> 00:27:46,418
- Espérate aquí.
- Sí.

280
00:27:56,015 --> 00:28:00,760
Mr Price. lt was all a misunderstanding.

281
00:28:00,895 --> 00:28:03,646
Your camera.

282
00:28:05,358 --> 00:28:07,599
l'm sorry.

283
00:28:20,247 --> 00:28:21,527
Passport.

284
00:28:21,665 --> 00:28:23,953
Before you go, you will sign some papers.

285
00:28:24,084 --> 00:28:28,496
- What papers?
- Your visitation papers, Mr Price.

286
00:28:28,629 --> 00:28:33,256
You were not arrested. You just came
to visit, in case your embassy asks.

287
00:28:34,218 --> 00:28:36,626
You want your passport back, yes?

288
00:28:44,728 --> 00:28:46,353
- You OK?
- l'm fine.

289
00:28:46,480 --> 00:28:49,896
- How'd you know where to find me?
- Where else? What happened?

290
00:28:50,025 --> 00:28:54,319
Oh, l was just visiting. Jazy was there.
l think he had me released.

291
00:28:54,446 --> 00:28:59,523
- Jazy? Think there's a story?
- l don't know. But l can start looking.

292
00:29:00,702 --> 00:29:04,035
- Looking for what?
- l'm gonna find Rafael.

293
00:29:09,502 --> 00:29:11,744
Now, Russel, we have
to be clever with Jazy.

294
00:29:11,879 --> 00:29:15,462
Don't worry. l won't come right out
and ask him if he's a spy or not.

295
00:29:15,591 --> 00:29:17,168
(Claire laughs)

296
00:29:17,468 --> 00:29:21,466
- Are you a spy or aren't you?
- Spy is such a nonword, Mr Price.

297
00:29:21,597 --> 00:29:26,010
- Nobody is a spy any more.
- Russel prefers pictures to words.

298
00:29:26,143 --> 00:29:29,060
You don't have to apologise.
You are journalists.

299
00:29:29,187 --> 00:29:32,603
- And you're a businessman?
- A businessman...

300
00:29:32,732 --> 00:29:36,184
That sounds good.
OK, l'm a businessman.

301
00:29:36,319 --> 00:29:40,233
Why was l arrested and then released?
Who the hell are you?

302
00:29:47,455 --> 00:29:51,073
- No water?
- No, no water.

303
00:29:51,209 --> 00:29:54,826
Marcel, you told me there'd be
water in the pool this week.

304
00:29:55,588 --> 00:29:59,751
lf she dove in, l assure you
she would not notice.

305
00:30:01,886 --> 00:30:08,553
My darling, the guerillas destroyed
the pumping station in Masaya.

306
00:30:09,059 --> 00:30:11,729
We must ration water for now.

307
00:30:12,062 --> 00:30:14,766
Maybe l should go back to Panama?

308
00:30:15,316 --> 00:30:17,521
Maybe you should.

309
00:30:17,651 --> 00:30:18,647
Please.

310
00:30:18,777 --> 00:30:20,852
Con permiso.

311
00:30:27,869 --> 00:30:32,744
You were arrested because the Guardia
are clowns who specialise in excess.

312
00:30:33,583 --> 00:30:37,201
You were released because
l told them to release you.

313
00:30:37,336 --> 00:30:39,044
Thank you.

314
00:30:39,172 --> 00:30:42,291
Those aren't the normal
duties of a businessman.

315
00:30:44,926 --> 00:30:47,797
But they are the normal duties of a spy.

316
00:30:49,556 --> 00:30:51,798
You win, l am a spy.

317
00:30:52,684 --> 00:30:55,389
There, are you happy? l feel better.

318
00:30:56,438 --> 00:30:59,723
Now we can relax.
You can turn off your little thing.

319
00:31:04,946 --> 00:31:07,780
Oh, l trust you won't say
anything to hurt me.

320
00:31:08,616 --> 00:31:10,858
Why would we wanna do that?

321
00:31:13,621 --> 00:31:16,076
ln some ways, l am a terrible spy.

322
00:31:17,625 --> 00:31:22,001
l used to be much better at it, but now
it seems everyone knows who l am.

323
00:31:23,088 --> 00:31:25,579
l have too many girlfriends.

324
00:31:25,716 --> 00:31:28,289
l like to be photographed.

325
00:31:28,427 --> 00:31:31,926
l talk too much. l always talk too much.

326
00:31:32,055 --> 00:31:34,676
But my girlfriends like that.

327
00:31:34,807 --> 00:31:37,381
- No matter.
- (woman) Marcel?

328
00:31:37,519 --> 00:31:41,219
- Do you know who she is?
- No.

329
00:31:41,356 --> 00:31:44,273
That's Miss Panama.
Do you know who that is?

330
00:31:44,401 --> 00:31:45,563
Yes, l do.

331
00:31:45,693 --> 00:31:48,185
She's in love with me.

332
00:31:50,698 --> 00:31:53,450
l've got to get some water in the pool.

333
00:31:54,077 --> 00:31:56,994
And once a week l have lunch
with President Somoza

334
00:31:57,121 --> 00:32:01,248
to discuss security measures
against the Sandinista insurgents,

335
00:32:01,375 --> 00:32:04,292
and all he wants to talk about
is Miss Panama.

336
00:32:05,170 --> 00:32:07,412
He is worried about her.

337
00:32:07,547 --> 00:32:13,004
- He thinks she's seeing another man?
- He assigned me to find out who he is.

338
00:32:15,430 --> 00:32:17,469
Thank you.

339
00:32:18,350 --> 00:32:21,386
We all know the revolutionaries
are going to win.

340
00:32:23,938 --> 00:32:25,978
Don't we?

341
00:32:28,735 --> 00:32:32,185
You know, l saw this picture
on a leaflet in Africa.

342
00:32:32,322 --> 00:32:34,360
You know what they all say about it?

343
00:32:34,490 --> 00:32:37,242
That you're the genius
that created that idea.

344
00:32:37,368 --> 00:32:39,824
lt was a lot of people's idea.

345
00:32:43,165 --> 00:32:45,786
Have you been to León?

346
00:32:45,918 --> 00:32:48,040
- No.
- No, we're going to Masaya.

347
00:32:48,169 --> 00:32:50,839
We understand the rebels
have entered the cuartel.

348
00:32:50,964 --> 00:32:56,504
You would love León.
A nice cathedral. Beautiful light.

349
00:32:56,720 --> 00:32:59,839
- We're not doing a travelogue.
- Of course, of course.

350
00:32:59,973 --> 00:33:04,599
Only l have heard that Comandante Rafael
was recently in the area.

351
00:33:04,895 --> 00:33:09,722
- Rafael's near León?
- Well, it's a rumour. What do l know?

352
00:33:09,857 --> 00:33:13,641
Marcel, estoy desamparada.

353
00:33:15,404 --> 00:33:18,820
- She's lonely.
- Well, we don't want to keep you.

354
00:33:18,949 --> 00:33:20,989
lt's my job.

355
00:33:21,118 --> 00:33:23,574
Do you think l talk too much?

356
00:33:30,460 --> 00:33:32,915
(Russel) So Rafael's near León.

357
00:33:38,134 --> 00:33:40,293
Did you dream about
Miss Panama last night?

358
00:33:40,428 --> 00:33:43,594
No. l dreamed about you.

359
00:33:44,474 --> 00:33:48,305
- Did you have a good time?
- Yeah. So did you.

360
00:33:52,023 --> 00:33:54,727
ls that an old war injury flaring up?

361
00:33:55,693 --> 00:33:58,480
- ls that tape recorder on?
- Absolutely.

362
00:33:59,280 --> 00:34:03,229
l was sunning myself on the USS Pueblo
when the North Koreans attacked.

363
00:34:03,367 --> 00:34:05,904
l took a bullet in the chest.
But l was lucky.

364
00:34:06,036 --> 00:34:09,239
l had a roll of Ektachrome
in my pocket here over my heart...

365
00:34:09,373 --> 00:34:12,824
And the bullet ricocheted
over the film and grazed your cheek...

366
00:34:12,959 --> 00:34:15,830
Saved my life. You heard about it, huh?

367
00:34:25,805 --> 00:34:29,850
- Do you ever dream about me?
- Yeah, once.

368
00:34:29,975 --> 00:34:32,015
How was it?

369
00:34:32,519 --> 00:34:34,394
Fast.

370
00:34:34,522 --> 00:34:37,012
- How fast?
- Real fast.

371
00:34:37,358 --> 00:34:39,599
You mean this fast?

372
00:34:45,240 --> 00:34:47,279
(camera clicking)

373
00:34:57,294 --> 00:34:59,701
That's another Rafael sign.

374
00:35:19,148 --> 00:35:21,187
(gunfire)

375
00:35:29,574 --> 00:35:32,243
LEÓN
PROVlNClAL CAPlTAL

376
00:35:32,369 --> 00:35:34,408
Bájense. Documentos.

377
00:35:50,553 --> 00:35:52,925
(gunfire)

378
00:36:08,612 --> 00:36:11,529
lt's June 10th. The evacuation of León.

379
00:36:12,783 --> 00:36:15,237
Signs for the FSLN are everywhere.

380
00:36:18,747 --> 00:36:20,786
(gunfire)

381
00:36:24,126 --> 00:36:26,368
A woman carries a pig.

382
00:36:32,552 --> 00:36:34,591
(man) Carlos!

383
00:37:14,383 --> 00:37:16,422
(explosion)

384
00:38:01,011 --> 00:38:03,253
Do you want photographs?

385
00:38:05,140 --> 00:38:07,382
Come with us.

386
00:38:10,771 --> 00:38:13,936
- You must help us one more time.
- For León, for Nicaragua.

387
00:38:14,065 --> 00:38:16,306
No, l don't want to.

388
00:38:21,030 --> 00:38:23,069
- Americans?
- Yes.

389
00:38:23,741 --> 00:38:25,199
Journalists, sí?

390
00:38:25,326 --> 00:38:27,733
Pedro, there's no time to waste.

391
00:38:36,670 --> 00:38:42,542
When you get back to the States, l want
you give this ball to Dennis Martinez,

392
00:38:42,676 --> 00:38:47,421
- from me, sí? Dennis Martinez, sí?
- Dennis Martinez.

393
00:38:47,931 --> 00:38:52,558
Enrique is dead. The Guardia control
the church and we need your help.

394
00:39:00,443 --> 00:39:02,352
Pedro.

395
00:39:07,616 --> 00:39:10,617
- You come. You come, huh?
- Yes.

396
00:39:10,744 --> 00:39:12,986
Use the back way.

397
00:39:46,195 --> 00:39:47,903
(aircraft)

398
00:39:48,030 --> 00:39:52,277
The Guardia have the stairs covered.
Go through the courtyard.

399
00:40:13,721 --> 00:40:14,717
(gunfire)

400
00:40:14,847 --> 00:40:17,303
lt's not safe. Come with me.

401
00:40:47,546 --> 00:40:49,787
Aquí, aquí. Rápido.

402
00:40:54,052 --> 00:40:56,091
Ahora! Fuego!

403
00:41:03,478 --> 00:41:05,516
Ahora, súbete!

404
00:41:34,466 --> 00:41:36,505
A la torre!

405
00:41:54,651 --> 00:41:56,728
Listo?

406
00:42:29,268 --> 00:42:31,675
(gunfire)

407
00:42:31,812 --> 00:42:34,267
- Por aquí.
- Ya los vi.

408
00:42:45,533 --> 00:42:48,450
Bring out your dead and wounded.

409
00:43:10,557 --> 00:43:12,929
Price, is that you?

410
00:43:15,020 --> 00:43:18,140
- You motherfucker, Price, is that you?
- Yeah.

411
00:43:18,523 --> 00:43:21,097
Where are those bastards?
They away?

412
00:43:22,819 --> 00:43:25,061
They're away.

413
00:43:35,456 --> 00:43:38,243
- You all right?
- Yeah. lt's not my blood.

414
00:43:39,085 --> 00:43:41,492
- Man, that kid's got a good arm.
- Yeah.

415
00:43:44,924 --> 00:43:49,135
- What the fuck are you doing here?
- What the fuck are you doing here?

416
00:43:51,388 --> 00:43:54,058
Man, my ears are freakin' out.

417
00:43:59,230 --> 00:44:01,471
You're lookin' good.

418
00:44:02,815 --> 00:44:06,861
- How do you like Nicaragua?
- lt's beautiful.

419
00:44:09,197 --> 00:44:12,198
Yeah, there's a shitload
of greasers, though.

420
00:44:13,868 --> 00:44:15,944
(man) No queda nadie.

421
00:44:16,078 --> 00:44:18,652
- Pricey, l'll see you later, man.
- Yeah.

422
00:44:20,207 --> 00:44:22,366
Se acabó, vámonos!

423
00:44:23,919 --> 00:44:25,959
- You OK?
- Yeah, l'm fine.

424
00:44:26,547 --> 00:44:28,705
The kid's got a hell of an arm.

425
00:44:28,840 --> 00:44:30,086
Sandy Koufax, no?

426
00:44:30,217 --> 00:44:33,302
- Gracias, padre.
- De nada. Vayan con Dios.

427
00:44:37,266 --> 00:44:39,507
Koufax was good.

428
00:44:39,643 --> 00:44:42,181
But Dennis Martinez, he is the best.

429
00:44:43,397 --> 00:44:45,638
He's from Nicaragua.

430
00:44:45,773 --> 00:44:48,062
He pitches major leagues.

431
00:44:48,985 --> 00:44:53,612
- l'd like to find Rafael.
- He was here, but he's gone.

432
00:44:53,740 --> 00:44:55,898
He's going to Matagalpa, no?

433
00:44:56,033 --> 00:44:59,367
You control a baseball
better than your words.

434
00:44:59,495 --> 00:45:02,579
Rafael cannot be found.
You understand, compañeros?

435
00:45:02,707 --> 00:45:04,948
What's Rafael doing in Matagalpa?

436
00:45:05,084 --> 00:45:07,290
Just keep your talk to baseball.

437
00:45:08,045 --> 00:45:12,506
You see Dennis Martinez,
you tell him that my curve ball is better,

438
00:45:12,632 --> 00:45:14,875
that l have a good scroogie.

439
00:45:16,177 --> 00:45:18,847
l like Sandinistas.

440
00:45:18,972 --> 00:45:21,428
And l like Baltimore Orioles.

441
00:45:24,102 --> 00:45:26,142
(Russel) You bastard!

442
00:45:39,993 --> 00:45:42,947
- What are we gonna do about him?
- He's dead.

443
00:46:15,610 --> 00:46:19,193
(Claire) You can't believe
everything you hear in the news.

444
00:46:19,321 --> 00:46:23,783
l think about you all the time.
l'll try and get back before you graduate.

445
00:46:23,909 --> 00:46:26,614
l love you very, very much.

446
00:46:26,745 --> 00:46:30,446
l'll finish this up back at the hotel, honey.
Bye-bye now.

447
00:46:54,563 --> 00:46:57,434
l know who shot Pedro.

448
00:46:59,819 --> 00:47:02,488
Somebody in the bell tower.

449
00:47:03,030 --> 00:47:07,608
- Why didn't you tell the guerillas?
- Because l knew they'd kill him.

450
00:47:10,787 --> 00:47:12,946
And l didn't wanna interfere.

451
00:47:19,296 --> 00:47:21,752
lt wasn't an easy choice.

452
00:47:26,678 --> 00:47:28,919
l think l made the wrong one.

453
00:47:36,062 --> 00:47:41,056
Do you know that you didn't shoot any
pictures after that whole thing was over?

454
00:47:43,402 --> 00:47:45,857
l didn't, did l?

455
00:47:49,533 --> 00:47:51,988
Oh, Jesus, l picked up the gun.

456
00:48:00,085 --> 00:48:02,541
ls something happening to us?

457
00:48:05,214 --> 00:48:07,457
Yeah, l think so.

458
00:48:08,968 --> 00:48:11,008
Yeah, l know.

459
00:50:06,164 --> 00:50:10,162
- How was Matagalpa?
- No bang-bang, Alex. None at all.

460
00:50:10,293 --> 00:50:13,662
- Did you find anything?
- Yeah. Half the press corps.

461
00:50:20,428 --> 00:50:22,467
Hello?

462
00:50:25,683 --> 00:50:27,591
Claire.

463
00:50:27,726 --> 00:50:29,765
Hey!

464
00:50:56,837 --> 00:50:59,080
- Alex.
- How you doing?

465
00:51:00,383 --> 00:51:02,837
- How was León?
- Bloody.

466
00:51:05,471 --> 00:51:07,677
Claire, l'm tired of Nicaragua.

467
00:51:07,806 --> 00:51:10,379
- You haven't been here very long.
- Yeah.

468
00:51:11,268 --> 00:51:13,307
Long enough.

469
00:51:14,270 --> 00:51:16,310
Long enough.

470
00:51:16,940 --> 00:51:19,431
You're right. Everybody's right.

471
00:51:21,069 --> 00:51:23,109
About what?

472
00:51:24,447 --> 00:51:27,982
My cheekbones.
What do you think of 'em?

473
00:51:29,786 --> 00:51:32,027
l like your cheekbones, Alex.

474
00:51:33,080 --> 00:51:35,452
ls there anything the matter?

475
00:51:35,582 --> 00:51:38,038
lt's a face made for television.

476
00:51:41,589 --> 00:51:44,126
You mean you decided
to go with the network?

477
00:51:44,257 --> 00:51:46,297
Yeah.

478
00:51:49,179 --> 00:51:52,264
They're gonna give me
ten grand a week to read the news.

479
00:51:52,390 --> 00:51:55,641
l'm gonna be in 60 million homes
every night.

480
00:51:55,769 --> 00:51:58,057
When l take a breath,
all of America will do so.

481
00:51:58,188 --> 00:52:01,972
When my voice trembles,
all of America will tremble.

482
00:52:02,108 --> 00:52:04,267
l'm gonna be a star.

483
00:52:05,695 --> 00:52:08,862
My voice will be more important
than who controls Congress.

484
00:52:08,990 --> 00:52:13,153
- You'll become a household name.
- l'll become a household name.

485
00:52:15,538 --> 00:52:18,372
l should never have come down here.

486
00:52:21,168 --> 00:52:25,461
l'm sorry, Alex.
l think it's a lot better this way.

487
00:52:25,589 --> 00:52:28,163
lt's all right. Don't worry about me.

488
00:52:30,469 --> 00:52:33,006
l'm speaking in song titles.

489
00:52:33,138 --> 00:52:36,970
- But promise me one thing.
- l'll promise you anything.

490
00:52:37,100 --> 00:52:41,311
No farewell parties. l don't wanna
make a speech to anyone.

491
00:52:44,232 --> 00:52:46,901
- Russel?
- Russel who?

492
00:52:48,736 --> 00:52:50,480
Him too.

493
00:53:52,547 --> 00:53:55,085
(♪ ''Cuando calienta el sol'' ♪)

494
00:54:11,774 --> 00:54:14,230
- Ça va bien?
- Comment ça va?

495
00:54:18,448 --> 00:54:22,444
You're running late, Mr President.
We can schedule this for another time.

496
00:54:22,576 --> 00:54:26,194
Nonsense. Let them wait.

497
00:54:29,541 --> 00:54:32,162
We are a stunning couple, huh?

498
00:54:32,293 --> 00:54:35,330
My stomach is like a rock.
l've been working out.

499
00:54:35,463 --> 00:54:37,503
Yes, we are a stunning couple.

500
00:54:38,759 --> 00:54:41,676
Mr President, you own
one fifth of the land in Nicaragua.

501
00:54:41,803 --> 00:54:44,590
You own the port, the airlines,
the Mercedes dealership...

502
00:54:44,722 --> 00:54:46,964
ls it a crime to be a car dealer?

503
00:54:47,600 --> 00:54:49,841
Let me show you something.

504
00:54:52,604 --> 00:54:56,437
lt's said that the Guardia operates
a torture chamber at Coyotepe.

505
00:54:56,567 --> 00:54:58,809
This is a portrait of my father.

506
00:54:59,528 --> 00:55:02,198
He was very special to me.

507
00:55:02,322 --> 00:55:06,949
Every Sunday morning l drive out to the
cemetery and put flowers on his grave.

508
00:55:07,077 --> 00:55:09,235
l think people should know that.

509
00:55:09,371 --> 00:55:11,992
Would you comment on
the fall of León to the rebels?

510
00:55:17,044 --> 00:55:21,506
Listen, Russel. Let's grow up, huh?
lt's easy to fall in love with the underdog,

511
00:55:21,632 --> 00:55:24,337
but there's an upside
and a downside to this thing.

512
00:55:24,469 --> 00:55:28,383
l just wanna remind you all this stuff
about a ''revolution of poets'' is crap.

513
00:55:28,514 --> 00:55:31,006
lt's great PR though, isn't it, Hub?

514
00:55:32,017 --> 00:55:34,425
So what's the upside?

515
00:55:34,562 --> 00:55:36,803
Simple, and it could happen.

516
00:55:36,939 --> 00:55:40,059
Somoza destroys the insurgents,
rebuilds the country,

517
00:55:40,192 --> 00:55:43,442
shitcans the purveyors of excess,
stabilises the cordoba,

518
00:55:43,570 --> 00:55:47,650
and is finally beloved as
the saviour of Nicaragua. Our pal.

519
00:55:47,783 --> 00:55:49,822
- You got a smoke?
- Yeah.

520
00:55:54,456 --> 00:55:58,239
- What's the downside?
- Commies take over the world.

521
00:56:00,461 --> 00:56:02,501
Señor Kittle.

522
00:56:09,387 --> 00:56:12,257
Excuse me, Russel,
but the war may be over.

523
00:56:15,434 --> 00:56:19,847
This is a democracy, and l have
been freely elected by my people.

524
00:56:21,023 --> 00:56:23,395
- There were more votes than voters...
- Presidente!

525
00:56:23,525 --> 00:56:27,737
No me ven que estoy ocupado
con esta señorita? Váyase de aquí.

526
00:56:33,118 --> 00:56:36,985
l am sorry. l have to conclude
this encounter. Something happened.

527
00:56:37,121 --> 00:56:39,493
l have many more questions,
Mr President...

528
00:56:39,624 --> 00:56:42,541
Did he tell you about his parents
and the graveyard?

529
00:56:42,668 --> 00:56:45,919
- Yes, l know about that, but l'd like to...
- Good, good.

530
00:57:16,910 --> 00:57:18,949
(applause)

531
00:57:28,129 --> 00:57:31,746
- l'll just make sure everything's set up.
- Sí, rápido.

532
00:57:41,350 --> 00:57:46,225
My friends, this gathering was not
supposed to be a press conference

533
00:57:46,354 --> 00:57:48,976
as much as a get-together.

534
00:57:49,107 --> 00:57:51,894
But l've just been handed
a piece of news.

535
00:57:52,569 --> 00:57:54,810
Rafael is dead.

536
00:57:56,740 --> 00:58:00,191
He has been killed in an ambush
near Matagalpa.

537
00:58:00,326 --> 00:58:02,817
- Mr President!
- How many people killed?

538
00:58:02,954 --> 00:58:06,239
Sorry, my friends. No questions, please.

539
00:58:06,374 --> 00:58:08,947
A press release is being prepared.

540
00:58:09,085 --> 00:58:11,124
Call Washington.

541
00:58:14,298 --> 00:58:15,958
What do you think?

542
00:58:16,091 --> 00:58:19,839
Tacho makes that speech about
every six months. Maybe he got lucky.

543
00:58:19,970 --> 00:58:22,840
- Hub, is this for real?
- Yeah, sure.

544
00:58:22,973 --> 00:58:28,346
Russel, excuse me, but Miss Panama
would like her picture taken with Tacho.

545
00:58:28,479 --> 00:58:31,514
- ln colour?
- OK. A little embarrassing, huh?

546
00:58:35,026 --> 00:58:37,149
Señor presidente.

547
00:58:37,278 --> 00:58:39,318
Listo, listo.

548
00:58:39,447 --> 00:58:41,855
That'll be fine right there.

549
00:58:44,284 --> 00:58:47,072
How in the hell could Tacho find Rafael?

550
00:58:47,871 --> 00:58:50,445
Russel, please. l have my hands full.

551
00:58:52,168 --> 00:58:54,493
That's fine right there.

552
00:58:54,628 --> 00:58:58,293
ls Tacho lying again?
They did kill him, didn't they?

553
00:58:58,966 --> 00:59:01,088
What do l know?

554
00:59:01,218 --> 00:59:03,792
Tacho needs a victory very badly.

555
00:59:03,929 --> 00:59:07,629
He needs to prove to Jimmy Carter
that he is still winning.

556
00:59:07,765 --> 00:59:10,387
The death of Rafael is the proof he needs.

557
00:59:10,518 --> 00:59:14,219
Carter doesn't need proof. He just sent
25 million in new arms to Tacho.

558
00:59:14,355 --> 00:59:16,598
No, no. He didn't.

559
00:59:17,525 --> 00:59:22,650
The State Department is getting nervous
about what is going on down here.

560
00:59:22,780 --> 00:59:25,152
En el sol, por favor.

561
00:59:29,245 --> 00:59:32,495
Pardon my French,
but whose fucking side are you on?

562
00:59:32,623 --> 00:59:36,668
- l work for everybody.
- That's a great job.

563
00:59:36,960 --> 00:59:40,626
l send messages to Jimmy and l tell him
that the revolution is a flood

564
00:59:40,756 --> 00:59:43,959
which cannot be stopped,
but it can be controlled.

565
00:59:44,968 --> 00:59:47,423
Nobody listens to me.

566
00:59:47,554 --> 00:59:50,424
l can't even get a little water in my pool.

567
00:59:51,391 --> 00:59:53,134
(Miss Panama giggles)

568
00:59:53,268 --> 00:59:56,470
Would you switch sides, please?
For just one more.

569
00:59:59,315 --> 01:00:01,806
That's very nice, very nice. Thank you.

570
01:00:03,444 --> 01:00:06,481
l think Rafael is alive. l'm gonna find him.

571
01:00:08,115 --> 01:00:09,859
Thank you very much.

572
01:00:10,409 --> 01:00:12,283
MATAGALPA
NORTHERN PROVlNCE

573
01:00:12,411 --> 01:00:14,450
(gunfire)

574
01:00:20,752 --> 01:00:24,038
- There's the guy we're lookin' for.
- Terrific.

575
01:00:36,392 --> 01:00:38,634
Go one more block.

576
01:00:43,691 --> 01:00:46,395
Oh, shit! l'm not gonna die in Matagalpa.

577
01:00:47,152 --> 01:00:49,144
Pare. Pare.

578
01:00:50,572 --> 01:00:52,398
Alto. Alto!

579
01:00:52,657 --> 01:00:55,326
- Calm down, Regis.
- l'm not stayin'!

580
01:00:57,161 --> 01:01:01,324
For Christ's sake, they wanted to look
at our credentials. What are you doing?

581
01:01:01,915 --> 01:01:05,366
Me escuchan?
Si va una combi, deténganla.

582
01:01:17,388 --> 01:01:19,713
Bájese! Alto!

583
01:01:21,975 --> 01:01:23,718
Get down!

584
01:01:29,232 --> 01:01:31,058
Jesus!

585
01:01:31,984 --> 01:01:34,190
Look out!

586
01:01:44,120 --> 01:01:46,159
Stop! Stop it!

587
01:01:54,379 --> 01:01:56,502
- Periodista.
- Televisión.

588
01:01:58,299 --> 01:02:00,339
Let's go!

589
01:02:09,393 --> 01:02:11,718
(Regis) Abre la puerta, por favor!

590
01:02:11,853 --> 01:02:13,893
Gracias, señora.

591
01:02:15,481 --> 01:02:17,059
You all right?

592
01:02:22,738 --> 01:02:24,777
Asesinos!

593
01:02:43,090 --> 01:02:44,584
Ahora.

594
01:02:44,716 --> 01:02:46,755
Aguante.

595
01:02:47,510 --> 01:02:49,550
Alto! Alto!

596
01:02:51,347 --> 01:02:52,806
Stay down.

597
01:04:05,080 --> 01:04:06,704
Libertad!

598
01:04:06,832 --> 01:04:08,990
(Russel) Periodista.

599
01:04:09,125 --> 01:04:11,165
- You all right?
- Yeah.

600
01:04:12,045 --> 01:04:13,954
Periodista.

601
01:04:21,678 --> 01:04:24,169
- Viva Rafael!
- Que viva!

602
01:04:48,995 --> 01:04:51,034
Entren.

603
01:05:05,051 --> 01:05:07,506
The translator from the hotel.

604
01:05:09,638 --> 01:05:11,678
You're looking for Rafael?

605
01:05:11,807 --> 01:05:15,057
- Yeah, if it's possible.
- How'd you know?

606
01:05:15,602 --> 01:05:19,931
Mr Price doesn't do anything before
announcing it first to the whole world.

607
01:05:20,064 --> 01:05:23,397
lt's a good story. You'll be more famous.

608
01:06:42,388 --> 01:06:44,428
Vengan, compañeros.

609
01:07:07,411 --> 01:07:09,652
What is it?

610
01:07:10,288 --> 01:07:12,744
Rafael is dead.

611
01:07:14,459 --> 01:07:16,831
- l can smell it.
- Vengan acá.

612
01:07:18,045 --> 01:07:20,287
Come on.

613
01:07:39,690 --> 01:07:42,097
What were you talking about?

614
01:07:42,234 --> 01:07:44,273
He's dead. l know it.

615
01:07:45,612 --> 01:07:48,067
(Claire) l wonder what they want with us.

616
01:07:48,323 --> 01:07:50,611
l don't know.

617
01:07:52,159 --> 01:07:54,199
No les he dicho nada.

618
01:07:56,205 --> 01:07:58,742
- This is Comandante Cinco.
- Es un placer.

619
01:07:58,874 --> 01:08:02,124
León has fallen
and today we took Matagalpa.

620
01:08:02,252 --> 01:08:04,493
Masaya is next and then Managua.

621
01:08:04,796 --> 01:08:07,251
Because Nicaragua
will soon be free, Mr Price,

622
01:08:07,381 --> 01:08:10,133
we've decided that it's time
for you to meet Rafael.

623
01:08:10,259 --> 01:08:14,470
- We need a photograph.
- The Western press needs a photograph.

624
01:08:14,596 --> 01:08:17,632
The world is not divided
into East and West any more.

625
01:08:17,766 --> 01:08:21,300
lt's divided into North and South.
Come with us.

626
01:09:04,892 --> 01:09:08,640
You're a great photographer.
Make him alive.

627
01:09:15,818 --> 01:09:17,193
(chuckles)

628
01:09:17,486 --> 01:09:19,894
Why are you laughing?

629
01:09:22,699 --> 01:09:24,656
You're crazy.

630
01:09:24,784 --> 01:09:29,411
We have momentum,
but many more lives will be lost.

631
01:09:30,123 --> 01:09:34,831
Even Washington is starting to admit
that Somoza is not loved by his people.

632
01:09:35,544 --> 01:09:39,209
They have detained $25 million
in new arms shipments to Somoza

633
01:09:39,339 --> 01:09:41,462
at an airfield in Florida,

634
01:09:41,591 --> 01:09:45,505
until they find out
if Rafael is alive or dead.

635
01:09:46,220 --> 01:09:51,178
lf Washington thinks Rafael is dead,
they will ship the arms to Somoza.

636
01:09:52,351 --> 01:09:54,806
Do you understand?

637
01:09:56,855 --> 01:09:58,894
Yes.

638
01:10:01,109 --> 01:10:05,153
- l'm a journalist.
- This has nothing to do with journalism.

639
01:10:05,279 --> 01:10:08,315
Enough of our people
have been lost already.

640
01:10:09,074 --> 01:10:11,992
We need to keep him alive
a few more days.

641
01:10:13,453 --> 01:10:17,616
Once the war is over, none of this matters.

642
01:10:25,631 --> 01:10:28,335
l don't do things like this.

643
01:10:30,343 --> 01:10:33,463
l know this is difficult for you,

644
01:10:33,596 --> 01:10:35,636
but you must do it.

645
01:10:44,731 --> 01:10:47,898
ln the morning, when there's better light.

646
01:10:49,861 --> 01:10:52,103
lt will be a great picture.

647
01:11:06,376 --> 01:11:09,293
lt sure would be
a prizewinner, wouldn't it?

648
01:11:10,421 --> 01:11:12,710
l've won enough prizes.

649
01:11:12,840 --> 01:11:15,082
But you haven't won a war.

650
01:11:16,468 --> 01:11:18,508
Are you sure?

651
01:11:29,438 --> 01:11:31,478
Foto muy complicado, huh?

652
01:11:39,989 --> 01:11:42,278
Yeah, it's complicated, all right.

653
01:11:42,408 --> 01:11:45,991
Do l go back and say l missed
the biggest story in the war?

654
01:11:47,955 --> 01:11:51,288
Do l go back and say that
l saw Rafael stone-cold dead?

655
01:11:56,713 --> 01:12:01,670
Or do l just say that we fell in love with
the guerillas because their cause was...

656
01:12:01,801 --> 01:12:03,840
Sympathetic?

657
01:12:04,678 --> 01:12:06,920
Yeah, sympathetic.

658
01:12:21,944 --> 01:12:24,399
Christ, what are we doing here?

659
01:13:47,229 --> 01:13:49,138
You.

660
01:13:49,272 --> 01:13:51,810
Más arriba.

661
01:13:51,942 --> 01:13:53,851
That's fine.

662
01:13:55,695 --> 01:13:57,734
Yeah, that's good.

663
01:14:26,890 --> 01:14:28,929
All right.

664
01:15:23,649 --> 01:15:25,688
Viva Rafael!

665
01:15:26,985 --> 01:15:29,025
Viva Rafael!

666
01:15:55,928 --> 01:15:57,967
Marcel.

667
01:16:00,224 --> 01:16:02,975
-  Le gusta?
- Mucho, mucho, mucho.

668
01:16:03,101 --> 01:16:05,141
Gracias.

669
01:17:16,959 --> 01:17:20,162
(Claire) Under a still, grey July sky...
Start again.

670
01:17:20,588 --> 01:17:23,921
Under a clear, steel Managua... Scratch it.

671
01:17:26,802 --> 01:17:32,092
President Somoza has ordered the air
force to bomb the capital under a sky of...

672
01:17:45,026 --> 01:17:47,066
- Hi.
- Hi.

673
01:17:49,864 --> 01:17:52,865
- Look.
- Oh, my God.

674
01:17:55,202 --> 01:17:59,034
- (Russel) What the hell is he doing here?
- l have no idea.

675
01:18:08,047 --> 01:18:11,213
(Regis) Can you frame me
with that smoke in the frame?

676
01:18:11,342 --> 01:18:13,714
- Yeah, we got the smoke.
- Well, roll it.

677
01:18:13,844 --> 01:18:15,717
Speed.

678
01:18:15,846 --> 01:18:18,087
This is Regis Seydor in Managua.

679
01:18:18,932 --> 01:18:23,261
This tiny nation of smouldering volcanoes
has erupted into a civil war.

680
01:18:23,686 --> 01:18:27,470
Fighting has broken out on the streets
of the capital for the first time...

681
01:18:27,606 --> 01:18:29,350
Hi.

682
01:18:29,483 --> 01:18:31,226
- Alex.
- Congratulations.

683
01:18:31,360 --> 01:18:33,352
- On what?
- ''On what?''

684
01:18:33,487 --> 01:18:37,187
The news services, the wire,
The Washington Post, The Times.

685
01:18:37,323 --> 01:18:39,861
Everybody's got it. lt's a fabulous picture.

686
01:18:39,992 --> 01:18:43,076
- Yes, it really is fabulous.
- Yeah, it is.

687
01:18:44,622 --> 01:18:47,456
- How come you're back?
- l came back to see Russel.

688
01:18:47,583 --> 01:18:49,990
See me? About what?

689
01:18:50,127 --> 01:18:54,539
The East Coast is in love with Rafael.
They were sure he was dead this time.

690
01:18:54,672 --> 01:19:00,377
They're gonna do a musical. You can't
move without seeing his mug on T-shirts.

691
01:19:00,511 --> 01:19:03,132
He's bigger than Farrah Fawcett.

692
01:19:03,263 --> 01:19:05,386
(explosion)

693
01:19:13,898 --> 01:19:15,974
You look great. Things OK?

694
01:19:16,108 --> 01:19:20,521
Things are great, yeah. l've never
been happier. You two, uh...?

695
01:19:20,654 --> 01:19:22,896
- Terrific.
- Yeah?

696
01:19:23,949 --> 01:19:26,819
Alex, you know me, l'm a little slow.

697
01:19:29,203 --> 01:19:31,908
Exactly why are you here?

698
01:19:32,039 --> 01:19:34,079
l wanna do an interview with Rafael.

699
01:19:34,208 --> 01:19:36,781
You're the only man
who can take me to him.

700
01:19:41,089 --> 01:19:43,544
- What's the matter?
- Nothin'.

701
01:19:58,396 --> 01:20:00,768
We may not be able
to find him, you know.

702
01:20:00,899 --> 01:20:03,472
l have supreme confidence in you.

703
01:20:07,321 --> 01:20:10,487
- Claire looks good.
- Everybody looks good in the tropics.

704
01:20:10,616 --> 01:20:12,857
What the hell does that mean?

705
01:20:17,580 --> 01:20:21,079
- Alex, l'm in love with her.
- l know, and she thinks she loves you.

706
01:20:21,209 --> 01:20:23,995
No, it's past the thinking stage.

707
01:20:24,128 --> 01:20:29,751
Can l ask you something? This probably
doesn't mean a goddamn thing, but...

708
01:20:29,883 --> 01:20:32,290
it's something that interests me.

709
01:20:32,427 --> 01:20:34,503
Were you guys making it
before we came here?

710
01:20:34,637 --> 01:20:35,882
No!

711
01:20:36,014 --> 01:20:38,172
- ls that the truth?
- Yes.

712
01:20:38,599 --> 01:20:41,469
For God's sakes, Alex. We're friends.

713
01:20:46,440 --> 01:20:48,681
OK.

714
01:21:00,244 --> 01:21:02,283
Alto. Alto.

715
01:21:06,374 --> 01:21:09,577
Periodista. Periodista.

716
01:21:09,711 --> 01:21:11,750
- Bájese!
- Prensa, prensa.

717
01:21:17,593 --> 01:21:19,632
Periodista.

718
01:21:26,476 --> 01:21:28,634
Periodista.

719
01:21:31,021 --> 01:21:33,061
Vamos.

720
01:21:33,607 --> 01:21:34,770
Vamos.

721
01:21:41,239 --> 01:21:43,278
Buenos días.

722
01:21:49,079 --> 01:21:53,492
- You must go through a lot of rental cars.
- Don't worry. l put it in your name.

723
01:21:55,502 --> 01:21:57,210
Give me your papers.

724
01:21:57,337 --> 01:21:59,376
(machine-gun fire)

725
01:22:11,683 --> 01:22:13,426
Come on, come on.

726
01:22:23,360 --> 01:22:26,147
Get those bodies on the truck... fast!

727
