01:50:50,855 --> 01:50:53,097
- Shut up!
- Don't move!

971
01:50:54,150 --> 01:50:55,774
lt's just a story.

972
01:50:55,901 --> 01:50:57,360
Shut your mouth.

973
01:50:57,486 --> 01:51:02,444
They say that if somebody is holding
a gun on you, you shouldn't stop talking.

974
01:51:02,574 --> 01:51:05,147
That's the theory.

975
01:51:05,285 --> 01:51:07,443
Who knows?

976
01:51:07,578 --> 01:51:11,029
Maybe it's a good thing
that l talk too much.

977
01:51:11,707 --> 01:51:13,534
(gunshot)

978
01:51:27,221 --> 01:51:29,095
(car horn)

979
01:51:32,351 --> 01:51:34,390
(gunfire)

980
01:51:35,896 --> 01:51:39,264
We gotta get outta here.
The whole fuckin' army's looking for me.

981
01:51:39,399 --> 01:51:41,557
Yeah. They're not looking for me.

982
01:51:42,193 --> 01:51:47,068
Let me take the film. lf l can't make it
back to the hotel, l'll come back here.

983
01:51:48,991 --> 01:51:52,739
Look, it's more dangerous
being with you than being alone.

984
01:51:54,579 --> 01:51:56,618
Right.

985
01:51:58,583 --> 01:52:00,908
Get the flag. We'll put the film in it.

986
01:53:51,476 --> 01:53:53,468
ls anyone there?

987
01:53:58,274 --> 01:54:01,856
- What is it?
- l need to get this to the hotel.

988
01:54:01,985 --> 01:54:04,227
Please come in.

989
01:54:37,768 --> 01:54:39,807
Russel!

990
01:54:41,438 --> 01:54:43,679
(helicopter overhead)

991
01:54:44,524 --> 01:54:46,563
Russel?

992
01:54:51,738 --> 01:54:53,197
Russel!

993
01:54:57,577 --> 01:54:59,616
(gunfire)

994
01:55:09,004 --> 01:55:11,043
(screaming)

995
01:55:15,260 --> 01:55:17,667
(announcement from helicopter)

996
01:55:31,024 --> 01:55:34,060
- Have you seen this man?
- No, l haven't.

997
01:55:34,861 --> 01:55:36,900
(horn)

998
01:55:37,822 --> 01:55:40,277
Abran paso!

999
01:56:27,283 --> 01:56:29,524
Lo ha visto?

1000
01:56:31,787 --> 01:56:33,826
No.

1001
01:56:47,092 --> 01:56:50,295
(TV) ..Russel Price,
un bien conocido foto-journalista

1002
01:56:50,429 --> 01:56:52,635
que estaba viajando con Grazier.

1003
01:56:52,764 --> 01:56:56,215
El presidente Somoza
ha cambiado su posición anterior,

1004
01:56:56,351 --> 01:56:59,636
y ahora dice que el tiroteo fue accidental.

1005
01:56:59,770 --> 01:57:03,768
Tacho, como Somoza es conocido
popularmente, ha regresado...

1006
01:57:41,975 --> 01:57:44,014
Journalist?

1007
01:57:45,061 --> 01:57:47,516
You knew the man who was killed?

1008
01:57:50,775 --> 01:57:53,265
50,000 Nicaraguans have died,

1009
01:57:54,153 --> 01:57:56,643
and now one Yankee.

1010
01:57:56,780 --> 01:58:01,027
Perhaps now Americans will be
outraged at what is happening here.

1011
01:58:03,536 --> 01:58:05,659
Perhaps they will.

1012
01:58:05,788 --> 01:58:12,075
Maybe we should have killed
an American journalist 50 years ago.

1013
01:59:09,804 --> 01:59:11,843
(helicopter)

1014
01:59:55,345 --> 01:59:59,805
1 7 July, 1 979 - President Anastasio
Somoza flees to Miami, Florida

1015
01:59:59,932 --> 02:00:02,886
with the bodies of his father and brother.

1016
02:00:39,385 --> 02:00:42,338
- Have you seen the Guardia?
- No, l haven't.

1017
02:00:42,471 --> 02:00:45,424
- ls the war over yet?
- l don't know.

1018
02:00:46,433 --> 02:00:48,888
The tanks are coming!

1019
02:01:36,394 --> 02:01:38,434
Russel?

1020
02:02:13,803 --> 02:02:17,337
(crowd chants) Rafael! Rafael! Rafael!

1021
02:02:35,739 --> 02:02:38,526
Rafael! Rafael! Rafael!

1022
02:02:46,958 --> 02:02:48,997
(band music and singing)

1023
02:03:01,346 --> 02:03:03,338
(Oates) Hey, Price.

1024
02:03:03,473 --> 02:03:05,512
Hey, Pricey!

1025
02:03:11,688 --> 02:03:14,144
lt's all over, huh? We made it.

1026
02:03:16,359 --> 02:03:18,850
l like this music.

1027
02:03:18,987 --> 02:03:21,275
What the hell are you doin' here?

1028
02:03:21,405 --> 02:03:23,362
lt's a free country.

1029
02:03:23,491 --> 02:03:26,242
l mean, it's free now, anyway.

1030
02:03:27,161 --> 02:03:30,446
Nica libre. Rum and Coke, no ice.
You want some?

1031
02:03:39,797 --> 02:03:42,502
You aren't gonna turn me in, are you?

1032
02:03:45,427 --> 02:03:47,550
See you in Thailand.

1033
02:04:10,700 --> 02:04:13,273
Do you think we fell in love
with too much?

1034
02:04:14,620 --> 02:04:17,075
l'd do it again.

